   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Salient-Mask Quantization — Google Colab Runner\n",
    "\n",
    "**Runtime**: `Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU` (free tier) or A100 (Colab Pro)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook:\n",
    "1. Clones the repo from GitHub\n",
    "2. Installs dependencies (skips torch — Colab already has it with CUDA)\n",
    "3. Verifies GPU availability\n",
    "4. Runs the GPT-2 experiment\n",
    "5. Displays results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step1-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Clone Repository\n",
    "\n",
    "Replace `YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME` with your GitHub username."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "clone",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "GITHUB_USERNAME = \"YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME\"  # <-- change this\n",
    "REPO_NAME = \"salient-quant\"\n",
    "REPO_URL = f\"https://github.com/{GITHUB_USERNAME}/{REPO_NAME}.git\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(REPO_NAME):\n",
    "    !git clone {REPO_URL}\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Repo already cloned — pulling latest changes\")\n",
    "    !cd {REPO_NAME} && git pull\n",
    "\n",
    "%cd {REPO_NAME}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step2-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "install",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q -r requirements_colab.txt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step3-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Verify GPU"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "check-gpu",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "if not torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    raise RuntimeError(\n",
    "        \"No GPU detected. Go to Runtime → Change runtime type → GPU and re-run.\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "gpu = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0)\n",
    "print(f\"GPU : {gpu.name}\")\n",
    "print(f\"VRAM: {gpu.total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB\")\n",
    "print(f\"CUDA: {torch.version.cuda}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step4-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 — Run Experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses `configs/gpt2_colab.yaml` (full calibration, full perplexity eval, no token cap).\n",
    "\n",
    "Runtime on a T4: ~10–15 min for GPT-2 small."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run-experiment",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!python experiments/run_experiment.py --config configs/gpt2_colab.yaml"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "step5-header",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5 — View Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "view-results",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json, glob\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "results_dir = Path(\"results/gpt2_colab\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load summary JSON if present\n",
    "summary_files = sorted(results_dir.glob(\"**/*.json\"))\n",
    "for f in summary_files:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n=== {f.name} ===\")\n",
    "    with open(f) as fh:\n",
    "        print(json.dumps(json.load(fh), indent=2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "view-plots",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "\n",
    "for png in sorted(glob.glob(\"results/gpt2_colab/plots/*.png\")):\n",
    "    print(png)\n",
    "    display(Image(png))"
   ]
  },
